              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2">Gunkk</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/16/2003&nbsp;: 3:00:11 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> You're right Wilmena ... at 58, you're hosed.  Too bad you didn't do Needlites in Echo in your 20s.  They hit insanely fast (delays in the low teens) and hit for max of 12 IIRC.  With Banshee Aura, they basically beat themselves to death.<br /><br />On a philosophical note... you souldn't be getting hit at level 58.  If you are, you're doing something wrong.  Maxing your defense won't mean squat for when you're hunting POP mobs who hit for 500-700.  If you get aggro and are within melee range, you're probably gonna be dead.  3500 HP and Force Shield only means you get two chances to FD when the mobs are hitting for 1500-2000 per round.  Maxed defence might make that 1400-1900 per round.  You'll still be dead in 2 rounds.<br /><br />Ok, now if you still really want to max your defense:  Find a light blue mob (level 45?) that hits for low numbers and hits fast.  Use pet-tanking.  Step in, get hit, step out, lifetap-dot/lifetap, rinse, repeat.  Use any and all STR/ATK/AC debuffs you can.  Crip-Claud, Succ of Shadows, Shadow Vortex (cast before SoS), Degeneration,  Strength Tap (if it stacks when cast before Degen), CoC, etc.  Slowing mobs just results in fewer hits to you and fewer skillup chances per hr.  Slowing only buys you the ability to channel through a lifetap.  Using a pet will be more efficient since you can step out and let Jabober take a few swings while you take more time to cast the more mana-efficient lifetap-dots.  Shieldskin is your friend... Jaspers are cheap HP.  Use them.<br /><br />Old world Monk NPCs are probably your best bet -- low ATK and fast, light hitters.  I disagree with Iltraendar's Nadox recommendation, LOY mobs hit WAY too hard, and are designed for post-luclin 50s warrior class AC levels.  200 hitters are definitely NOT for casters.  Not sure but EJ mosquitoes might be worth it if they're anything like Echo Needlites.  <br /><br />*MAX* your AC.   Drop some pp for a gear purchase or two and don't forget a Virtue from your local POK cleric whore.  Even if the mobs "miss" you can still get skillups.  Or &lt;gasp&gt; make a friend with a druid who can cast a decent DS and heal you when pulling multiples.<br /><br />Good luck!<br /><br /></span></font></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top"
